  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6565 sitting right above the massive -11360M negative gamma wall at 6550, dealers are in full amplification mode and will aggressively buy any dips toward that strike while selling strength into the 6600 positive gamma ceiling. The concentrated negative gamma cluster between 6540-6560 creates a volatile amplification zone where dealer flow will exaggerate moves in both directions, making this a high-risk area for choppy, trending price action. Key levels: defend 6550 for upside continuation, break below triggers accelerated selling into 6540, while any push toward 6600 faces heavy dealer selling pressure.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect wild swings between 6550-6600 with dealers amplifying every move.",
